Interface ThrowingShortFunction1<R>

    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ThrowingShortFunction1<R>
extends AbstractThrowingShortFunction1<R,AbstractThrowingShortFunction1.Handler<R>>
    Represents a function that accepts a short-valued argument and produces a result or throws a throwable. This is the one-arity specialization of ThrowingToShortFunctionN. This is the short-consuming primitive specialization of ThrowingFunction1. This is the throwing variation of ShortFunction1.

    This is a functional interface whose functional method is AbstractThrowingShortFunction1.apply(short).

    Since:
    1.0.0
    See Also:
    ThrowingFunction1, ThrowingToShortFunctionN, ShortFunction1
